You can define [Pattern replace char filter][1] with custom analyzer. this will add the `_a` with all the token generated and you not need to update it in Java code. 

```json
POST _analyze
{
  &quot;text&quot;: [
    &quot;Stack overflow&quot;
  ],
  &quot;tokenizer&quot;: &quot;standard&quot;, 
  &quot;char_filter&quot;: [
    {
      &quot;type&quot;: &quot;pattern_replace&quot;,
      &quot;pattern&quot;: &quot;(\\S+)&quot;,
      &quot;replacement&quot;: &quot;$0_a&quot;
    }
  ]
}
```

**Output:**
```json
{
  &quot;tokens&quot; : [
    {
      &quot;token&quot; : &quot;Stack_a&quot;,
      &quot;start_offset&quot; : 0,
      &quot;end_offset&quot; : 5,
      &quot;type&quot; : &quot;&lt;ALPHANUM&gt;&quot;,
      &quot;position&quot; : 0
    },
    {
      &quot;token&quot; : &quot;overflow_a&quot;,
      &quot;start_offset&quot; : 6,
      &quot;end_offset&quot; : 14,
      &quot;type&quot; : &quot;&lt;ALPHANUM&gt;&quot;,
      &quot;position&quot; : 1
    }
  ]
}

```

  [1]: https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/analysis-pattern-replace-charfilter.html

