e.g., elsewhere on SO: &lt;a href=&quot;https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2148686/non-public-top-level-class-vs-static-nested-class&quot;&gt;**Non-public top-level class** vs static nested class&lt;/a&gt;

As for changes in behavior between versions, there was this discussion about something that &quot;worked perfectly&quot; in 1.2.2. but stopped working in 1.4 in sun&#39;s forum: &lt;a href=&quot;http://forums.sun.com/thread.jspa?threadID=248432&amp;tstart=2211&quot;&gt;Java Compiler - unable to declare a non public top level classes in a file&lt;/a&gt;.

