In this case it does skip action, ie it leaves out reading &quot;age&quot;. It can also handle cases like a field changes from int to long etc..

This is a very nice article explaining schema evolution - http://martin.kleppmann.com/2012/12/05/schema-evolution-in-avro-protocol-buffers-thrift.html

2. Schema is stored only once for multiple records in a single file.

3. Size, encoded in very few bytes.

